Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{}, add @salt{0.25%tsp} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the saucepan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the saucepan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Finely chop the @chives{1} (or use #scissors{} if you like!). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve the @red chilli{0.5} lengthways, de-seed and finely slice.

> Leave the chilli out if you don't like heat.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{0.5%425g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the @pork sausage meat{225%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up while it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the pepper to the pan and cook, stirring, until it starts to soften, another ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%400g can}, @chicken stock powder{1} and @water{} (see ingredients for amount) to the pan. Stir to dissolve the stock powder. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @soured cream{75%g} in a #small bowl{} and stir in half the chives. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Taste the chilli and add more salt and pepper if needed. Add the kidney beans and bring back to a simmer.

> If there are any bean-haters, keep some of the chilli bean-free.

Serve the rice and chilli in #bowls{} with a dollop of sour cream, a sprinkling of the remaining chives and some sliced red chilli (for the adults). Sprinkle over the cheese. Enjoy!